        "calculation": {
            "id": "calculation",
            "title": "Calculations",
            "isApplicable": true,
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "For both the low-pass and high-pass filters, the desired cutoff frequency (fc) is 10 kHz. The standard formula for cutoff frequency is:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "f_c = \\frac{1}{2\\pi RC}"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Rearranging to solve for capacitance C:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "C = \\frac{1}{2\\pi R f_c}"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Substituting R = 5.6 kΩ and fc = 10 kHz:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "C = \\frac{1}{2\\pi \\times 5.6 \\times 10^3 \\times 10 \\times 10^3} \\approx 2.84\\,\\text{nF}"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Hence, the required capacitor value is approximately 2.8 nF. Since a single 2.8 nF capacitor was unavailable in the lab, two 5.6 nF capacitors were connected in series to achieve the equivalent value:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "C_{eq} = \\frac{C}{2} = \\frac{5.6\\,\\text{nF}}{2} = 2.8\\,\\text{nF}"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Since R1 = Rf = 5.6 kΩ and the circuit is an inverting amplifier, the voltage gain is:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "A_v = -\\frac{R_f}{R_1} = -\\frac{5.6\\,\\text{k}\\Omega}{5.6\\,\\text{k}\\Omega} = -1"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "At the cutoff frequency, the gain drops by a factor of 1/√2, so the magnitude of gain at cutoff is:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "|A_{v_{\\text{cutoff}}}| = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} \\approx 0.707"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The negative sign indicates a 180° phase shift, which is expected in inverting amplifier configurations."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Measured gain verification at cutoff (LPF):**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "|A_{v_{\\text{measured}}}| = \\frac{V_{out}}{V_{in}} = \\frac{700\\,\\text{mV}}{1\\,\\text{V}} = 0.7"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Measured gain verification at cutoff (HPF):**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "equation",
                    "value": "|A_{v_{\\text{measured}}}| = \\frac{V_{out}}{V_{in}} = \\frac{752\\,\\text{mV}}{1\\,\\text{V}} = 0.752"
                }
            ]
        },
